525875\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104att1665702875221.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/att1665702875221.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/att1665702875221.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"att1665702875221\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Unicode in Uniface Applications\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"att1665702875221__unicode_in_uniface_applications_92972\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Unicode characters can be used in fields, variables, parameters, and the user interface, but there are some restrictions.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"att1665702875221__p_d28349e1_d28350e1_d28351e1\">In Uniface applications, Unicode characters can be used in:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14525e1_d14526e1_d14527e1\">String data fields, variables, and parameters.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14528e1_d14529e1_d14530e1\">String literals in the user interface, such as labels, menu items, and component titles.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14531e1_d14532e1_d14533e1\">String parameters passed between the application and other components; for example, file I/O, or calling a WebService.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"att1665702875221__p_d28352e1_d28353e1_d28354e1\">Uniface provides the <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> packing code for string fields to contain Unicode characters, and a ProcScript function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span> to generate Unicode characters from their codes.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"att1665702875221__p_d28355e1_d28356e1_d28357e1\">There are some restrictions in using Unicode characters:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14534e1_d14535e1_d14536e1\">The first 128 Unicode characters (the ASCII characters) can be used everywhere in Uniface as long as the name conventions are satisfied; for example, control characters cannot be part of the object's names.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14537e1_d14538e1_d14539e1\">The remaining Unicode characters:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14540e1_d14541e1_d14542e1\">Are allowed in widgets, Unifields, initial values, and menu items.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14543e1_d14544e1_d14545e1\">Are not allowed as object names, such as component names, entity names, and field names.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14546e1_d14547e1_d14548e1\">Are allowed when passing string parameters to a non-Uniface component, if the component is Unicode-based such as Java.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"att1665702875221__li_d14549e1_d14550e1_d14551e1\">If you use non-ASCII characters in an assignment file, you need to save it in the Unicode (UTF-16 or UTF-8) encoding.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"att1665702875221__p_d28358e1_d28359e1_d28360e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dpa1665702875291.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dpa1665702875291.html\" title=\"Although Uniface supports Unicode and the installable character sets, there are restrictions in using them.\">Restrictions on Use of Unicode and Installable Character Sets</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525875\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525875\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Unicode in Uniface Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Unicode in Uniface Applications Unicode characters can be used in fields, variables, parameters, and the user interface, but there are some restrictions. In Uniface applications, Unicode characters can be used in: String data fields, variables, and parameters. String literals in the user interface, such as labels, menu items, and component titles. String parameters passed between the application and other components; for example, file I/O, or calling a WebService. Uniface provides the W packing code for string fields to contain Unicode characters, and a ProcScript function $string to generate Unicode characters from their codes. There are some restrictions in using Unicode characters: The first 128 Unicode characters (the ASCII characters) can be used everywhere in Uniface as long as the name conventions are satisfied; for example, control characters cannot be part of the object's names. The remaining Unicode characters: Are allowed in widgets, Unifields, initial values, and menu items. Are not allowed as object names, such as component names, entity names, and field names. Are allowed when passing string parameters to a non-Uniface component, if the component is Unicode-based such as Java. If you use non-ASCII characters in an assignment file, you need to save it in the Unicode (UTF-16 or UTF-8) encoding. For more information, see Restrictions on Use of Unicode and Installable Character Sets . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}